### recipe-finder — sample requests (target behavior)
### Open in IntelliJ / VS Code "REST Client", or translate to curl.
@host = http://localhost:8095

### 1. Search recipes by name
GET {{host}}/api/recipes/search?q=chicken

### 1b. Search with no match -> expect empty list, NOT 404
GET {{host}}/api/recipes/search?q=zzzznotarealdish

### 2. Recipe details (Teriyaki Chicken Casserole) -> note ingredient Map
GET {{host}}/api/recipes/52772

### 2b. Unknown meal id -> expect 404
GET {{host}}/api/recipes/00000000

### 3. Random recipe (same full structure as #2)
GET {{host}}/api/recipes/random

### 4. Recipes by category
GET {{host}}/api/recipes/category/Seafood

### 5. All categories
GET {{host}}/api/categories

### Resiliency / observability
GET {{host}}/actuator/health

### Swagger UI (open in browser)
# {{host}}/swagger-ui/index.html

# ---- curl equivalents ----
# curl "http://localhost:8095/api/recipes/search?q=chicken"
# curl "http://localhost:8095/api/recipes/52772"
# curl "http://localhost:8095/api/recipes/random"
# curl "http://localhost:8095/api/recipes/category/Seafood"
# curl "http://localhost:8095/api/categories"
# curl "http://localhost:8095/actuator/health"
